Frontal sclerite oval, with long, slender ventral projection (Fig. 
3K
). Eyes (Fig. 
3I
) contiguous. Antennal flagellum (Fig. 
3M
) brown, with sculpture, flagellomere 13 with apical projection; AR 1.01. Clypeus (Fig. 
3N
) with five pairs of setae. Palpus (Fig. 
3O
) brown; third segment slender, PR 2.70, lengths of palpus segments in ratio of 3: 6: 14: 6: 8.
